  <body>
    <p>
      - Gambling winning can go on 1040
    </p>
    <p>
      - Gambling income is UN-earned income
    </p>
    <p>
      - NON-resident aliens are subject to flat 30% tax rate.
    </p>
    <p>
      - For US citizens casino has mandated 24% withholding
    </p>
    <p>
      
    </p>
    <p>
      - <span style="font-weight: bold;">You may be eligible relief if</span>:
    </p>
    <p>
      1. filed a joint return
    </p>
    <p>
      2. Your taxes were understated due to errors
    </p>
    <p>
      3.&#160;You didn't know about the errors
    </p>
    <p>
      4. You're no longer married or living together
    </p>
    <p>
      
    </p>
    <p>
      <span style="font-weight: bold;">You're no longer married or living together if any of these apply:</span>
    </p>
    <p>
      1. You're legally separated, divorced or widowed
    </p>
    <p>
      2.&#160;NO longer in the same household for 12 months before request.
    </p>
    <p>
      
    </p>
    <p>
      - See: <span style="font-weight: bold;">Innocent Spouse relief</span>:
    </p>
    <p>
      1. One party is innocent of a mistake made by the other,
    </p>
    <p>
      2. limited to ONLY un-married people,
    </p>
    <p>
      3. <span style="font-weight: bold;">Form 8857</span>
    </p>
    <p>
      
    </p>
    <p>
      - See <span style="font-weight: bold;">Injured Spouse relief</span>:
    </p>
    <p>
      1. One party is hurt by the others past debts,
    </p>
    <p>
      2. TP is NOT responsible for others debt,
    </p>
    <p>
      3. <span style="font-weight: bold;">Form 8379</span>
    </p>
  </body>
