<richcontent TYPE="NODE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      <span style="font-weight: bold;">AOC, American Oppurtunity Credit </span>
    </p>
    <p>
      <span style="font-weight: bold;">============================== </span>
    </p>
    <p>
      <span style="font-weight: bold;">SEE Pub 970 - Tax Benefits for Education </span>
    </p>
    <p>
      <span style="font-weight: bold;">Form 1098-T required. </span>
    </p>
    <p>
      <span style="font-weight: normal;">Form 8862&#160;&#160;For American opportunity Credit. </span>
    </p>
    <p>
      <span style="font-weight: normal;">Credit of up to $2,500 (2000 + 25% after 2K). </span>
    </p>
    <p>
      <span style="font-weight: normal;">Can ONLY be used for UNDERGRAD first 4 years. </span>
    </p>
    <p>
      <span style="font-weight: normal;">Single=$90K, MFJ=$180K. </span>
    </p>
    <p>
      <span style="font-weight: normal;">NOT MFS. </span>
    </p>
    <p>
      <span style="font-weight: normal;">MUST be in Degree Prog, &gt;= half time. </span>
    </p>
    <p>
      <span style="font-weight: normal;">NO Felony Drug convictions. </span>
    </p>
    <p>
      <span style="font-weight: normal;">40% of credit may be refundable. </span>
    </p>
    <p>
      <span style="font-weight: normal;">NOT nonresident aliens </span>
    </p>
    <p>
      <span style="font-weight: normal;">Used for Tuition, Fees, Books, NOT Room &amp; Board or Health INS.</span>
    </p>
    <p>
      
    </p>
    <p>
      <span style="font-weight: bold;">Lifetime Learning Credit </span>
    </p>
    <p>
      <span style="font-weight: bold;">===================== </span>
    </p>
    <p>
      <span style="font-weight: normal;">Up to $2K</span>
    </p>
    <p>
      <span style="font-weight: normal;">Does not need to be in degree prog. </span>
    </p>
    <p>
      <span style="font-weight: normal;">OK for felony drug charges </span>
    </p>
    <p>
      <span style="font-weight: normal;">NOTE: Student doesn't report scholarship as income on the tax return</span><span style="font-weight: bold;">. </span>
    </p>
    <p>
      
    </p>
    <p>
      <span style="font-weight: normal;">NOTE: </span><span style="font-weight: bold;">Early IRA Distributions CAN BE USED for Education(Exception) </span>
    </p>
    <p>
      <span style="font-weight: bold;">- Student/Family can take IRA distributions for qualified higher education expenses without having to pay </span>
    </p>
    <p>
      <span style="font-weight: bold;">the 10% additional tax.</span>
    </p>
  </body>
</html>

</richcontent>
